We receive groups of up to 7 people, we have excellent facilities to provide comfort to families, travelers or groups that come to Bogota for reasons of study or business and others.
Heaps of information about Bogota and Colombia from our friendly bi-lingual staff
Immaculately clean hostel thanks to our tireless 24 hour team of staff members (some of which may end up feeling like your mum away from home);
Daily organised activities to show you the best of Bogota;
Sociable bar serving the most delicious cocktails and beers at reasonable prices! (open Monday to Saturday, 6-12pm - giving you the option to party on outside or get a good nights sleep);
The hottest showers in South America (well if travel guides says it, it must be true);
Free breakfast daily and Colombian coffee served all day;
Free and fully equipped communal kitchen;
Our sociable (read: party addict) owner is well connected to often get hostel guests free entry to the best parties in Bogota;
Free luggage storage and lockers;
Free Wi-Fi, free computers with Skype and free headsets for you to call home;
24 Security staff in a well-lit street for your safety;
Free local phone calls;
Printing for that last minute plane ticket confirmation;
2 LCD TVs with Satellite cable and unlimited access to our free extensive DVD library;
Clean, comfortable beds made up daily by our staff, and extra blankets when you need;
24 hour reception for constant attention;
Book exchange at a fair 1 for 1 rate;
BBQ and hammocks in the beautiful courtyards for your use;
Quick, thorough and well-priced laundry service;
Beauty therapists on call for manicures, pedicures, haircuts and massages.
